
[1]diabolical

   DIABOLIC, DIABOLICAL, a. [L., the devil.] Devilish; pertaining to the
   devil; hence, extremely malicious; impious; atrocious; nefarious;
   outrageously wicked; partaking of any quality ascribed to the devil; as
   a diabolical temper; a diabolical scheme or action.
